Heat the oil in small frying pan. Add the onion and cook for 3–4 minutes.Add the pork, garlic (if using) and mushrooms and cook for 2–3 minutes.Pour in the stock, cover with a lid and cook over a low heat for 5–10 minutes, or until the pork is cooked through.Remove from the heat, stir in the crème fraîche and chives, if using, and season to taste.Cook the courgetti in a microwave on high for 2 minutes. Leave to stand for 1 minute.Serve the pork and sauce with the courgetti.